1
00:00:34,311 --> 00:00:35,984
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> <i>A great pally once said,</i>

2
00:00:36,147 --> 00:00:40,027
<i>"Christmas is a day that holds
all time together."</i>

3
00:00:40,184 --> 00:00:42,289
<i>I never really
believed it before now.</i>

4
00:00:42,420 --> 00:00:43,490
<i>People take from Christmas</i>

5
00:00:43,654 --> 00:00:45,861
<i>their memories of
happy times and sad,</i>

6
00:00:46,023 --> 00:00:48,128
<i>past, present and future.</i>

7
00:00:48,292 --> 00:00:50,499
<i>A moment on this one,
special day</i>

8
00:00:50,661 --> 00:00:54,507
<i>could forever change
how you see everything.</i>

9
00:00:57,468 --> 00:00:59,038
<font color="#808080">BOY:</font> <i>Dear, Santa...</i>

10
00:01:00,571 --> 00:01:04,383
<i>♪ I have a secret Christmas wish</i>

11
00:01:04,542 --> 00:01:07,421
<i>♪ I know you know it well</i>

12
00:01:07,578 --> 00:01:11,025
<i>♪ It's something that
I want so much</i>

13
00:01:11,182 --> 00:01:14,163
<i>♪ I cannot even tell</i>

14
00:01:14,318 --> 00:01:17,891
<i>♪ If I believe
with all my heart</i>

15
00:01:18,055 --> 00:01:21,696
<i>♪ I know it can come true</i>

16
00:01:21,859 --> 00:01:25,602
<i>♪ But if that never happens</i>

17
00:01:25,763 --> 00:01:31,770
<i>♪ Still I'll always
believe in you ♪</i>

18
00:01:33,671 --> 00:01:36,675
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> <i>Sweet, eh?
We'll get to that kid later.</i>

19
00:01:39,009 --> 00:01:42,980
<i>For me, my memories of Christmas
will never be quite the same again.</i>

20
00:01:43,180 --> 00:01:46,093
<i>All I wanted to be
was something else.</i>

21
00:01:46,250 --> 00:01:48,594
<i>Something better
than I thought! was.</i>

22
00:01:48,752 --> 00:01:51,790
<i>This is my story.
And it's all true.</i>

23
00:01:51,956 --> 00:01:53,560
<i>- My name is Bernard.</i>
<font color="#D900D9">(SNORING)</font>

24
00:01:53,724 --> 00:01:55,567
<i>And I'm an elf.</i>

25
00:01:57,061 --> 00:01:58,404
<font color="#D900D9">(EXCLAIMS)</font>

26
00:01:58,562 --> 00:02:00,906
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS, MUTTERING)</font>

27
00:02:01,065 --> 00:02:03,238
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

28
00:02:05,803 --> 00:02:07,305
Oh, no!

29
00:02:07,471 --> 00:02:09,917
Mint chocolate cookies,
I slept in!

30
00:02:11,041 --> 00:02:12,520
Not today, not today!

31
00:02:19,950 --> 00:02:21,793
Oh, where the blinking...?

32
00:02:21,952 --> 00:02:24,057
Ah, there you are.

33
00:02:25,089 --> 00:02:26,796
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL EXCLAIMING)</font>

34
00:02:26,957 --> 00:02:28,493
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font> No pants!

35
00:02:56,086 --> 00:02:59,829
Wait! Wait up!
<font color="#D900D9">(TRAIN WHISTLING)</font>

36
00:03:03,661 --> 00:03:05,038
Wait up!

37
00:03:05,196 --> 00:03:06,800
Hold the train!

38
00:03:07,431 --> 00:03:09,342
Oh! <font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

39
00:03:11,869 --> 00:03:13,542
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font> Huh?

40
00:03:21,845 --> 00:03:23,381
<font color="#D900D9">(EXCLAIMS)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL GASP)</font>

41
00:03:23,547 --> 00:03:25,925
Ah! Thanks!

42
00:03:26,116 --> 00:03:27,720
Merry Christmas!

43
00:03:34,158 --> 00:03:35,432
Excuse me, sorry!

44
00:03:35,626 --> 00:03:37,333
Excuse me, coming through!

45
00:03:37,494 --> 00:03:39,838
Excuse me! Excuse me!

46
00:03:39,997 --> 00:03:41,738
Oh, sorry!

47
00:03:44,802 --> 00:03:46,076
Morning, Blitz!

48
00:04:04,054 --> 00:04:06,056
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

49
00:04:16,667 --> 00:04:19,238
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Still no sign of the
North Pole, Mr. Baddington.

50
00:04:19,403 --> 00:04:23,715
<font color="#D900D9">(GROWLING)</font> Where are you, fat man?

51
00:04:23,874 --> 00:04:26,946
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL GASP)</font>
What are you staring at?

52
00:04:27,111 --> 00:04:28,112
Do something useful

53
00:04:28,279 --> 00:04:30,316
and get my mother on the com.
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR SLAMS)</font>

54
00:04:31,181 --> 00:04:33,127
There will be no need for that.

55
00:04:33,584 --> 00:04:37,555
Mother, what a
delightful surprise.

56
00:04:37,721 --> 00:04:40,031
You look even more
radiant than ever.

57
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:42,466
Luminous and brilliant,

58
00:04:42,626 --> 00:04:46,369
like a... a...
newly-bloomed rose,

59
00:04:46,497 --> 00:04:49,103
shimmering with dew
in the morning...

60
00:04:49,266 --> 00:04:52,406
That's enough bottom-snogging
from you, boy.

61
00:04:52,569 --> 00:04:54,378
This is hardly a pleasure trip.

62
00:04:54,538 --> 00:04:57,417
Need I remind you that you have
a shipping empire to run?

63
00:04:57,574 --> 00:04:59,952
Since you have taken the
Quickest Airborne Delivery,

64
00:05:00,110 --> 00:05:03,887
the only thing you have
managed to deliver is failure.

65
00:05:04,048 --> 00:05:08,497
Of course. It's still marvelous
to finally have you here.

66
00:05:08,652 --> 00:05:10,097
Put a sock in it!

67
00:05:10,254 --> 00:05:13,098
Christmas Eve is the busiest
day of the year for us,

68
00:05:13,257 --> 00:05:18,764
and here you are, chasing
a mystical, flying elf!

69
00:05:25,302 --> 00:05:27,179
I'm here for the presentation.

70
00:05:27,338 --> 00:05:29,978
- Name.
- Bernard D. Elf.

71
00:05:30,140 --> 00:05:31,983
- You're late!
- I know, I'm sorry.

72
00:05:32,142 --> 00:05:34,122
My alarm clock was broken
and I forgot my pants.

73
00:05:34,278 --> 00:05:37,623
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>
Yeah, I'm wearing them now.

74
00:05:37,781 --> 00:05:40,022
- Down the hall, back...
- Thanks!

75
00:05:40,184 --> 00:05:41,629
You're out of time.

76
00:05:41,785 --> 00:05:43,230
And <i>voila!</i>

77
00:05:43,420 --> 00:05:45,798
With my electrified
chipmunk decoy,

78
00:05:45,956 --> 00:05:48,994
unwanted Christmas tree guests
will be a thing of the past.

79
00:05:49,159 --> 00:05:51,867
One little nuzzle
of the nose, and he'll...

80
00:05:52,029 --> 00:05:54,771
Good morning, everyone!
<font color="#D900D9">(YELPING)</font>

81
00:05:56,266 --> 00:05:58,644
Uh... Oops.

82
00:05:58,802 --> 00:06:00,804
Uh, sorry I'm a bit late.

83
00:06:00,971 --> 00:06:03,975
I'm sorry, Bernard, but
you've missed your time slot.

84
00:06:04,141 --> 00:06:06,348
- Missed your time slot.
- Please?

85
00:06:06,510 --> 00:06:09,787
I've been working all year on
this invention. It's my best yet!

86
00:06:09,913 --> 00:06:13,986
Better than the mind eraser
invention from last year?

87
00:06:16,653 --> 00:06:19,429
Santa sightings, unavoidable, right?

88
00:06:19,623 --> 00:06:20,829
Maybe.

89
00:06:20,991 --> 00:06:23,995
But what if we could erase them forever?

90
00:06:24,161 --> 00:06:25,162
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPING)</font>

91
00:06:25,329 --> 00:06:29,209
Let's imagine that this
toy doll is a little girl

92
00:06:29,366 --> 00:06:30,868
who's just seen Santa.

93
00:06:31,034 --> 00:06:34,243
Now, one quick zap...

94
00:06:34,405 --> 00:06:36,681
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL YELLING)</font>

95
00:06:38,642 --> 00:06:43,091
Who are you and why are you wearing
that ridiculous elf costume?

96
00:06:43,247 --> 00:06:46,023
- Hey, I'm wearing one, too.
- Me, too.

97
00:06:46,183 --> 00:06:48,390
- We're all wearing them.
- Where are we?

98
00:06:48,552 --> 00:06:51,431
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> Some kind of
Christmas nightmare.

99
00:06:51,588 --> 00:06:53,534
<font color="#808080">WOMAN 2:</font> What is Christmas?

100
00:06:53,690 --> 00:06:56,933
- It took us months to recover.
- Months to recover.

101
00:06:57,094 --> 00:07:01,099
Poor Nutmeg still can't
remember his own name sometimes.

102
00:07:01,265 --> 00:07:03,370
Isn't that right, Nutmeg?

103
00:07:06,703 --> 00:07:08,444
- See?
<font color="#808080">BERNARD:</font> - Please!

104
00:07:08,605 --> 00:07:10,676
I've worked on this
all year long.

105
00:07:10,841 --> 00:07:12,787
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> - No.
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> - Say no. Say no.

106
00:07:12,943 --> 00:07:16,755
<font color="#808080">MAN 2:</font> - Don't do it.
- You've got one minute.

107
00:07:16,914 --> 00:07:18,120
Thank you.
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL GROANING)</font>

108
00:07:18,282 --> 00:07:20,785
<font color="#D900D9">(CLEARS THROAT)</font> Ask yourselves,

109
00:07:20,951 --> 00:07:25,661
what is the one thing Santa
can't fit into his bag?

110
00:07:27,558 --> 00:07:29,697
The answer, of course, is...

111
00:07:29,860 --> 00:07:31,362
...memories!

112
00:07:31,528 --> 00:07:34,031
Christmas memories, to be exact.

113
00:07:34,198 --> 00:07:36,769
Every year, millions are created,

114
00:07:36,934 --> 00:07:38,277
but where do they go?

115
00:07:38,435 --> 00:07:41,075
The get lost in our brains.

116
00:07:41,238 --> 00:07:44,776
And my machine locks on to
our happiest Christmas memory

117
00:07:44,942 --> 00:07:47,286
and projects it
right in front of us.

118
00:07:47,444 --> 00:07:50,721
Exactly what purpose
does this serve?

119
00:07:50,881 --> 00:07:53,293
Raising people's Christmas
spirits, of course.

120
00:07:53,450 --> 00:07:55,657
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES, CLEARS THROAT)</font>
I need a volunteer.

121
00:07:55,819 --> 00:07:58,060
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL SCREAMING)</font> Ooh!

122
00:08:01,859 --> 00:08:04,339
I'm not going. Let go!
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

123
00:08:05,162 --> 00:08:06,835
Minty, thanks for volunteering.

124
00:08:08,966 --> 00:08:10,912
<font color="#D900D9">(WHIMPERS)</font>

125
00:08:11,068 --> 00:08:12,604
Oooh.

126
00:08:12,769 --> 00:08:14,806
<font color="#D900D9">(BUZZING)</font> <font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

127
00:08:16,573 --> 00:08:19,918
Great Grand-elf's
chocolate-chunk cookies!

128
00:08:20,043 --> 00:08:23,047
<font color="#D900D9">(GIGGLES)</font> They were my favorite.

129
00:08:23,247 --> 00:08:25,022
- Oh!
- Oh, this is great.

130
00:08:25,182 --> 00:08:28,026
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CLAMORING)</font>

131
00:08:28,185 --> 00:08:29,528
Don't be a cinnamon twist!

132
00:08:30,220 --> 00:08:31,961
<font color="#D900D9">(DEVICE HUMMING)</font>

133
00:08:33,457 --> 00:08:36,370
My first Christmas kiss.

134
00:08:36,527 --> 00:08:38,268
Give me that!

135
00:08:40,631 --> 00:08:43,441
<font color="#D900D9">(CACKLING)</font> Yes!
Yee-haw!

136
00:08:43,567 --> 00:08:46,207
Ooh, this isn't so hard.

137
00:08:46,370 --> 00:08:48,748
<font color="#D900D9">(SPLUTTERING)</font>
Sir, please, careful.

138
00:08:48,939 --> 00:08:50,247
No, no, no, don't do that.

139
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:54,354
Let me. No, no, no!
No, not now!

140
00:08:54,511 --> 00:08:56,320
Oh, man!

141
00:09:01,652 --> 00:09:04,861
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL MURMURING)</font>
Ah! Back on.

142
00:09:05,022 --> 00:09:08,231
Just a small, uh, power surge.

143
00:09:08,392 --> 00:09:10,394
Can you believe those Christmas lights?
<font color="#D900D9">(NERVOUS CHUCKLE)</font>

144
00:09:10,561 --> 00:09:12,165
One goes out, they all go out.

145
00:09:12,329 --> 00:09:15,572
- That will be all, Bernard.
- All, Bernard!

146
00:09:15,732 --> 00:09:17,541
But it worked.
It worked, you saw...

147
00:09:17,701 --> 00:09:20,477
And merry Christmas to you.

148
00:09:21,238 --> 00:09:23,809
Yes, sir.
Merry Christmas to you.

149
00:09:23,974 --> 00:09:25,920
And I'd better not see you back here

150
00:09:26,076 --> 00:09:29,922
with another one of your
hare-brained inventions.

151
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:32,424
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

152
00:09:32,583 --> 00:09:36,224
Santech is only for
the greatest elf minds, not...

153
00:09:36,386 --> 00:09:40,266
<font color="#D900D9">(INHALES)</font>
...reindeer poop-scoopers.

154
00:09:41,325 --> 00:09:42,702
<font color="#808080">GUARD:</font> Poor fellow.

155
00:09:42,859 --> 00:09:46,204
Poor fellow? He caused a
blackout on Christmas Eve.

156
00:09:49,566 --> 00:09:50,738
Piece of junk.
<font color="#D900D9">(ZAPPING)</font>

157
00:09:50,901 --> 00:09:52,403
Ow!

158
00:09:53,337 --> 00:09:55,112
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

159
00:09:57,841 --> 00:10:00,151
<font color="#D900D9">(DEVICE LANDS)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN GRUNTS)</font>

160
00:10:13,090 --> 00:10:15,366
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

161
00:10:32,776 --> 00:10:34,653
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS, SNIFFS)</font>

162
00:10:40,917 --> 00:10:42,487
Hi, Dasher, hi, Dancer,

163
00:10:42,653 --> 00:10:44,394
Prancer, Vixen...

164
00:10:44,554 --> 00:10:48,593
Hi, Comet, hi, Cupid. Hi...

165
00:10:48,759 --> 00:10:50,170
Donner, where's Blixen?

166
00:10:50,327 --> 00:10:52,500
<font color="#D900D9">(GIBBERISH)</font> Ooh!

167
00:10:52,663 --> 00:10:55,041
<font color="#D900D9">(STRAINING)</font> You're on
my gingerbread basket!

168
00:10:55,232 --> 00:10:58,042
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKING GIBBERISH)</font>

169
00:10:58,201 --> 00:10:59,805
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

170
00:10:59,970 --> 00:11:02,075
That thing still won't
translate to English, eh?

171
00:11:02,205 --> 00:11:05,482
Oh, jingle bells,
I can't do anything right.

172
00:11:06,109 --> 00:11:08,680
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKING GIBBERISH)</font>

173
00:11:08,845 --> 00:11:11,189
If you're asking how
the presentation went,

174
00:11:11,348 --> 00:11:12,827
prepare to be underwhelmed.

175
00:11:12,983 --> 00:11:15,361
As usual, I'm a miserable failure.

176
00:11:15,519 --> 00:11:19,296
My Christmas memory machine
knocked the power out in the room.

177
00:11:19,456 --> 00:11:21,697
So embarrassing.

178
00:11:21,858 --> 00:11:24,862
But I guess I'll just have
to face the Christmas music.

179
00:11:25,028 --> 00:11:29,306
I'll never be one of
Santa's trusty inventors.

180
00:11:29,466 --> 00:11:31,207
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

181
00:11:33,503 --> 00:11:35,346
<font color="#D900D9">(DOOR OPENING)</font>

182
00:11:37,140 --> 00:11:39,313
<font color="#D900D9">(CLEARING THROAT)</font>

183
00:11:39,476 --> 00:11:42,685
Ah! Mr. Claus, I'm so sorry,
sir. I'll get that right off.

184
00:11:42,846 --> 00:11:44,883
Ho, ho, ho!
That's nothing!

185
00:11:45,048 --> 00:11:48,154
You fly around the world behind
eight well-fed reindeer,

186
00:11:48,318 --> 00:11:50,525
as long as I have and...
<font color="#D900D9">(GUFFAWS)</font>

187
00:11:50,687 --> 00:11:54,533
...and you get used to getting
hit with a few warm brownies.

188
00:11:55,859 --> 00:11:58,772
Say, what's this nifty contraption?

189
00:11:58,962 --> 00:12:00,464
It's a reindeer vocalizer.

190
00:12:00,630 --> 00:12:03,133
<font color="#D900D9">(BROADCASTING GIBBERISH)</font>

191
00:12:03,266 --> 00:12:06,873
You made this?
How clever.

192
00:12:07,037 --> 00:12:08,948
It would be if I could
get it to speak English.

193
00:12:09,139 --> 00:12:11,141
Merry Christmas, Blitzen.

194
00:12:11,308 --> 00:12:13,049
Are you ready to fly tonight?

195
00:12:13,210 --> 00:12:14,917
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKING GIBBERISH)</font>

196
00:12:15,078 --> 00:12:16,386
See?

197
00:12:16,546 --> 00:12:20,187
<font color="#D900D9">(SANTA RESPONDING IN GIBBERISH)</font>

198
00:12:20,350 --> 00:12:21,590
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKING GIBBERISH)</font>

199
00:12:28,258 --> 00:12:32,331
Works for me, I speak
all languages. Ho, ho, ho!

200
00:12:32,496 --> 00:12:34,942
Put down the brush
and come with me.

201
00:12:35,098 --> 00:12:37,271
There's something
I want to show you.

202
00:12:37,434 --> 00:12:42,281
Do you know there are tens of millions
of children who celebrate Christmas?

203
00:12:42,439 --> 00:12:45,215
Every year.
When I started,

204
00:12:45,375 --> 00:12:47,548
there were only a few thousand.

205
00:12:47,711 --> 00:12:49,884
Ever heard how I do it?

206
00:12:50,046 --> 00:12:52,458
Well, just rumors, sir.

207
00:12:52,616 --> 00:12:54,857
I haven't been snooping,
if that's what you mean,

208
00:12:55,018 --> 00:12:56,554
I swear, I don't go near the sleigh.

209
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:58,757
Except to admire it, of course.

210
00:12:58,922 --> 00:13:00,902
And I found a cup holder,
which is a nice feature,

211
00:13:01,057 --> 00:13:02,263
but I don't look at
anything else, so...

212
00:13:02,425 --> 00:13:05,429
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font> I know.
You're a good egg.

213
00:13:05,595 --> 00:13:09,566
Go on. How do you
think I do it? Hmm?

214
00:13:10,066 --> 00:13:14,378
Well, uh... Some of the guys
think you teleport.

215
00:13:14,538 --> 00:13:17,576
That theory isn't
scientifically sound.

216
00:13:17,741 --> 00:13:19,379
Now, time travel, on the other hand...

217
00:13:19,543 --> 00:13:22,422
Oh, you're one clever little elf!

218
00:13:22,579 --> 00:13:25,458
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>
You know your stuff. <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

219
00:13:25,615 --> 00:13:28,653
Santech's very first invention:

220
00:13:28,819 --> 00:13:31,493
the Time Globe.

221
00:13:31,655 --> 00:13:34,135
Absolutely tip-top secret.

222
00:13:34,291 --> 00:13:36,134
It's what started it all.

223
00:13:36,293 --> 00:13:39,274
Heh. Wouldn't be able
to keep up with my deliveries

224
00:13:39,429 --> 00:13:42,808
- if it weren't for this.
- It's real!

