<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE CLAMORING)</font>

444
00:25:57,900 --> 00:25:59,038
<font color="#808080">BERNARD:</font> Listen to me!

445
00:25:59,201 --> 00:26:01,647
Santa! Blitz, it's...

446
00:26:03,806 --> 00:26:06,184
Oh, you are unbelievable!

447
00:26:06,342 --> 00:26:09,016
Santa! <font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

448
00:26:10,980 --> 00:26:12,152
Santa!

449
00:26:14,016 --> 00:26:15,689
They're coming to get you,
Santa, you're in danger!

450
00:26:15,851 --> 00:26:17,524
Santa!
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

451
00:26:18,754 --> 00:26:21,325
Lump of coal in the stocking.
Threat neutralized.

452
00:26:21,490 --> 00:26:23,060
Nice tackle, partner.

453
00:26:23,225 --> 00:26:24,727
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

454
00:26:27,563 --> 00:26:29,941
You! You're the one who...

455
00:26:30,099 --> 00:26:32,705
Take this marshmallow head
back to base for questioning.

456
00:26:32,868 --> 00:26:34,745
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING, MUFFLED)</font>

457
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:40,284
<font color="#D900D9">(MUFFLED YELLING)</font>
You're making a big mistake!

458
00:26:40,443 --> 00:26:41,786
I need to warn Santa.

459
00:26:41,944 --> 00:26:44,288
Someone's coming and they're
after the Time Globe!

460
00:26:44,447 --> 00:26:47,189
Let me go! Santa!
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

461
00:26:48,618 --> 00:26:49,619
<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE CLAMORING)</font>
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Santa, sir.

462
00:26:49,785 --> 00:26:51,560
Your beard stylist had to cancel.

463
00:26:51,721 --> 00:26:52,927
He has the chimney flu.

464
00:26:53,089 --> 00:26:54,591
Would you like me to reschedule?

465
00:26:58,961 --> 00:27:01,441
Blitz, over here!

466
00:27:01,597 --> 00:27:04,407
Listen, you have to find the other me.

467
00:27:04,567 --> 00:27:07,480
I should be on my way to Santech
for the presentation right now.

468
00:27:07,637 --> 00:27:11,278
You have to convince me to warn
everybody about the invasion.

469
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:14,387
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKING GIBBERISH)</font>

470
00:27:14,543 --> 00:27:16,887
I don't know what that means.
But do whatever it takes.

471
00:27:17,013 --> 00:27:20,256
Do you understand? Stop me and get me
to listen to you no matter what!

472
00:27:20,416 --> 00:27:22,293
This is more important
than the presentation.

473
00:27:22,451 --> 00:27:24,692
Santa is in real danger!

474
00:27:24,887 --> 00:27:26,457
<font color="#808080">BERNARD 1:</font> Excuse me. Coming through!

475
00:27:26,622 --> 00:27:28,156
<font color="#808080">BERNARD 2:</font> - There I am!
- Oh, sorry!

476
00:27:28,157 --> 00:27:29,966
Go, go!

477
00:27:41,837 --> 00:27:43,646
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

478
00:27:43,806 --> 00:27:45,808
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

479
00:27:49,745 --> 00:27:51,247
Where am I?

480
00:27:51,380 --> 00:27:53,121
The Christmas Defense Department.

481
00:27:53,649 --> 00:27:55,129
The Christmas De-who
and the what now?

482
00:27:55,251 --> 00:27:57,162
You know how Santa knows
when you are sleeping?

483
00:27:57,319 --> 00:28:00,163
And knows when you're awake?
That's us!

484
00:28:00,322 --> 00:28:03,633
I'm Agent Snowy and you, little elf,

485
00:28:03,793 --> 00:28:05,534
have a lot of explaining to do.

486
00:28:05,695 --> 00:28:07,333
Well, I know what this looks like.

487
00:28:07,496 --> 00:28:11,672
But there is a perfectly
logical explanation.

488
00:28:11,834 --> 00:28:15,179
- I'm listening.
- First off, I'm from the future.

489
00:28:15,337 --> 00:28:17,214
Just to put that out there.

490
00:28:20,776 --> 00:28:22,278
I believe him.
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

491
00:28:26,115 --> 00:28:27,651
I'm being the good cop.

492
00:28:28,951 --> 00:28:30,191
Agent Shortbread!

493
00:28:30,352 --> 00:28:32,730
Do you have his naughty
or nice record up yet?

494
00:28:32,888 --> 00:28:35,198
Just one second.
<font color="#D900D9">(COMPUTERS HUMMING)</font>

495
00:28:35,357 --> 00:28:37,166
Let's see...

496
00:28:37,326 --> 00:28:40,205
Bernard D. Elf. Hmm.

497
00:28:40,362 --> 00:28:42,774
Height: three feet.
Favorite candy: gumdrops.

498
00:28:42,965 --> 00:28:46,970
Occupation...
poop-shoveler.

499
00:28:47,136 --> 00:28:49,377
<font color="#D900D9">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>
Director of Droppings.

500
00:28:49,538 --> 00:28:52,747
- Excuse me?
- I prefer "Director of Droppings."

501
00:28:52,908 --> 00:28:54,410
"Disposal Administrator."

502
00:28:54,577 --> 00:28:56,215
I am a professional, after all.

503
00:28:56,378 --> 00:28:58,415
This one's a real piece of work.

504
00:28:58,581 --> 00:29:01,221
- Claims to be from the future.
<i>- Uh, everyone, can I...</i>

505
00:29:01,383 --> 00:29:03,522
<font color="#D900D9">(SHORTBREAD)</font> Something
about a Time Globe.

506
00:29:03,686 --> 00:29:05,996
If there were such a thing
as a time travel globe,

507
00:29:06,155 --> 00:29:08,897
which we cannot confirm
or deny the existence of,

508
00:29:09,058 --> 00:29:10,696
how would you know of its existence?

509
00:29:10,860 --> 00:29:13,033
If it were to exist.
Hmm?!

510
00:29:13,195 --> 00:29:16,642
That is the most confusing
question I've ever heard.

511
00:29:18,267 --> 00:29:20,679
Answer it!
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

512
00:29:20,836 --> 00:29:23,112
- Santa showed me.
- Would Santa confirm

513
00:29:23,272 --> 00:29:24,683
that he showed you the Time Globe?

514
00:29:24,807 --> 00:29:27,913
He hasn't shown me it yet.
He showed it to me

515
00:29:28,077 --> 00:29:30,751
after I caused the blackout
in the Santech building.

516
00:29:30,913 --> 00:29:34,554
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font> Oh, this just
keeps getting better!

517
00:29:34,717 --> 00:29:36,890
And when, exactly,
does that happen?

518
00:29:37,052 --> 00:29:39,032
Hmm?
<font color="#D900D9">(ALARM BLARING)</font>

519
00:29:39,188 --> 00:29:42,260
- What's going on?
- Any minute now.

520
00:29:42,424 --> 00:29:45,268
We've got a problem.
We've got no power anywhere.

521
00:29:45,427 --> 00:29:47,930
The cloaking device is down.
Were exposed!

522
00:29:48,097 --> 00:29:51,476
I need more power!

523
00:30:00,643 --> 00:30:04,557
Sir, I think the equipment
is malfunctioning.

524
00:30:04,713 --> 00:30:06,784
- I'm... I'm getting a blop.
- You mean a blip?

525
00:30:06,949 --> 00:30:10,988
No, sir, it's a blop. It's far
too large to be a blip.

526
00:30:11,153 --> 00:30:14,293
Put it onscreen for Mommy.

527
00:30:17,092 --> 00:30:20,301
Mommy, there it is!
The North Pole!

528
00:30:20,462 --> 00:30:22,772
Let me see.

529
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:26,081
What are you talking about?

530
00:30:26,235 --> 00:30:28,476
I don't see any North Pole.

531
00:30:28,637 --> 00:30:31,140
What? Impossible.

532
00:30:32,675 --> 00:30:36,145
<font color="#D900D9">(SARCASTIC LAUGH)</font>
Oh, look. Nothing!

533
00:30:36,312 --> 00:30:38,986
No workshop. No sleigh.
No secrets.

534
00:30:39,148 --> 00:30:40,684
More failure?

535
00:30:40,850 --> 00:30:42,852
<font color="#D900D9">(SHEEPISH LAUGH)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH GASP)</font>

536
00:30:43,018 --> 00:30:46,522
If you do not have Santa's
sleigh by midnight tonight,

537
00:30:46,689 --> 00:30:49,636
you are cut off!
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

538
00:30:49,792 --> 00:30:51,294
You'll be living on a deserted island

539
00:30:51,460 --> 00:30:52,632
when I'm through with you.

540
00:30:52,795 --> 00:30:54,706
Is that clear?

541
00:30:54,864 --> 00:30:57,367
I will find it, Mommy.

542
00:30:57,533 --> 00:30:59,809
And all of the secrets it holds.

543
00:30:59,969 --> 00:31:04,679
Then QAD will truly be the quickest
package delivery service...

544
00:31:06,842 --> 00:31:08,480
...in the world.

545
00:31:11,313 --> 00:31:13,350
Find that blip.

546
00:31:13,515 --> 00:31:17,463
That... That thing
that we saw on the radar.

547
00:31:17,620 --> 00:31:20,863
Take me there now!
Whoa!

548
00:31:25,661 --> 00:31:28,141
<font color="#D900D9">(POWER GRID HUMMING)</font>

549
00:31:29,732 --> 00:31:30,870
It's working.

550
00:31:31,033 --> 00:31:32,979
Power is restored to the hologram.

551
00:31:33,135 --> 00:31:36,344
- Were we seen?
- It's too early to tell.

552
00:31:36,505 --> 00:31:38,644
Looks like you were right, Bernard.

553
00:31:38,807 --> 00:31:39,808
Bernard?

554
00:31:40,809 --> 00:31:43,187
He's getting away!

555
00:31:43,345 --> 00:31:45,188
Hold it right there!

556
00:31:45,347 --> 00:31:48,521
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH GRUNTING)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(ALARM BLARING)</font>

557
00:31:49,685 --> 00:31:51,130
Don't let him get away!

558
00:31:52,988 --> 00:31:54,194
<font color="#D900D9">(GUMDROP)</font> Get back here!

559
00:31:58,994 --> 00:32:00,200
Which way did he go?

560
00:32:06,902 --> 00:32:08,779
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN SNIFFING)</font> Cookie breath!

561
00:32:08,938 --> 00:32:10,417
He went that way!

562
00:32:10,572 --> 00:32:12,552
<font color="#D900D9">(ELEVATOR BUTTONS DINGING)</font>

563
00:32:29,525 --> 00:32:32,199
- What the...?
- Hah! Found you!

564
00:32:32,361 --> 00:32:34,307
Get him!

565
00:32:36,031 --> 00:32:37,533
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

566
00:32:41,303 --> 00:32:43,214
Get over here, you little...

567
00:32:43,372 --> 00:32:46,376
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL STRAINING)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

568
00:32:46,542 --> 00:32:48,613
<font color="#808080">COMPUTER VOICE:</font> <i>Welcome to the Mail-evator.</i>

569
00:32:48,777 --> 00:32:51,280
<font color="#D900D9">(CHRISTMAS CAROL PLAYING)</font>

570
00:32:54,950 --> 00:32:57,590
<font color="#D900D9">(BUZZING)</font>
<font color="#808080">COMPUTER:</font> <i>Elevator out of service.</i>

571
00:32:59,388 --> 00:33:00,765
<font color="#D900D9">(BUZZING)</font>

572
00:33:02,925 --> 00:33:04,529
<font color="#808080">COMPUTER:</font> <i>Elevator operational.</i>

573
00:33:04,727 --> 00:33:06,832
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLS)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING)</font>

574
00:33:10,599 --> 00:33:12,977
<font color="#D900D9">(HOLLERING)</font>

575
00:33:17,106 --> 00:33:20,053
<font color="#D900D9">(MUSIC FALTERS, STOPS)</font>

576
00:33:21,643 --> 00:33:22,815
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

577
00:33:22,978 --> 00:33:24,787
And I'd better not see you back here

578
00:33:24,947 --> 00:33:28,326
with another one of your
hare-brained inventions.

579
00:33:28,484 --> 00:33:31,124
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

580
00:33:31,286 --> 00:33:35,257
Santech is only for the
greatest elf minds, not...

581
00:33:35,424 --> 00:33:38,803
<font color="#D900D9">(INHALES)</font>
...reindeer poop-scoopers.

582
00:33:40,629 --> 00:33:42,006
<font color="#808080">GUARD:</font> Poor fellow.

583
00:33:42,164 --> 00:33:45,008
Poor fellow? He caused a
blackout on Christmas Eve.

584
00:33:46,802 --> 00:33:48,873
It was me.

585
00:33:49,038 --> 00:33:51,245
Piece of junk!
<font color="#D900D9">(ZAPPING)</font>

586
00:33:51,440 --> 00:33:52,544
Ow!

587
00:33:55,844 --> 00:33:57,346
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

588
00:33:57,513 --> 00:33:58,958
<font color="#D900D9">(DEVICE LANDS)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(MAN GRUNTS)</font>

589
00:34:00,783 --> 00:34:04,287
They found the North Pole
because of me.

590
00:34:05,220 --> 00:34:07,291
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

591
00:34:11,326 --> 00:34:13,306
<i>♪ What kind of an elf</i>

592
00:34:13,462 --> 00:34:15,442
<i>♪ Runs away to sulk</i>

593
00:34:15,631 --> 00:34:17,907
<i>♪ When he's not the best?</i>

594
00:34:18,067 --> 00:34:19,842
<i>♪ Who bumbles along</i>

595
00:34:20,002 --> 00:34:24,382
<i>♪ Wearing last night's
dinner on his vest?</i>

596
00:34:24,540 --> 00:34:26,645
<i>♪ Insists that he's smart</i>

597
00:34:26,809 --> 00:34:31,383
<i>♪ When all other elves
declare he's dim?</i>

598
00:34:31,547 --> 00:34:36,860
<i>♪ A kind of an elf like him</i>

599
00:34:38,253 --> 00:34:41,257
<i>♪ Head in the clouds, Bernard</i>

600
00:34:41,423 --> 00:34:44,404
<i>♪ Heart on the floor</i>

601
00:34:44,560 --> 00:34:47,439
<i>♪ Best to go back
to the place you belong</i>

602
00:34:47,596 --> 00:34:50,941
<i>♪ Back where you were before</i>

603
00:34:51,100 --> 00:34:54,047
<i>♪ Time to regroup, Bernard</i>

604
00:34:54,203 --> 00:34:57,241
<i>♪ Time to repair</i>

605
00:34:57,406 --> 00:34:59,386
<i>♪ Time to go back to the poop</i>

606
00:34:59,541 --> 00:35:01,214
<i>♪ And the shoveling scoop</i>

607
00:35:01,376 --> 00:35:04,414
<i>♪ And that whiff in the air</i>

608
00:35:04,580 --> 00:35:06,753
<i>♪ That's where the future me</i>

609
00:35:06,915 --> 00:35:11,022
<i>♪ Will turn to them and say</i>

610
00:35:11,186 --> 00:35:14,360
<i>- ♪ Even a flea
- ♪ What kind of an elf</i>

611
00:35:14,523 --> 00:35:19,563
<i>♪ Doesn't realize when
the world's gone wrong</i>

612
00:35:19,728 --> 00:35:23,471
<i>♪ Who flounders around
like a dying fish</i>

613
00:35:23,632 --> 00:35:25,805
<i>- ♪ To a silly song
- ♪ And even that crow</i>

614
00:35:25,968 --> 00:35:29,347
<i>♪ You're best to rely on an elf</i>

615
00:35:29,538 --> 00:35:32,417
<i>- ♪ Like me
- ♪ Like me</i>

616
00:35:32,574 --> 00:35:34,611
<i>- ♪ Never give up
- ♪ Which is who that elf</i>

617
00:35:34,776 --> 00:35:36,517
<i>♪ Aspires to be</i>

618
00:35:36,712 --> 00:35:38,385
<i>♪ What kind of an elf</i>

619
00:35:38,547 --> 00:35:42,120
<i>♪ Doesn't shy away
from a mucky task?</i>

620
00:35:42,284 --> 00:35:44,787
<i>♪ What kind of an elf</i>

621
00:35:44,953 --> 00:35:48,799
<i>♪ Answers "Yes!"
no matter what you ask</i>

622
00:35:48,957 --> 00:35:50,664
<i>♪ What kind of an elf</i>

623
00:35:50,826 --> 00:35:55,241
<i>♪ Has the wherewithal
to put this right</i>

624
00:35:55,397 --> 00:36:01,279
<i>♪ An elf who'll
fight and never flee</i>

625
00:36:01,436 --> 00:36:07,443
<i>♪ A kind of an elf like me ♪</i>

626
00:36:20,289 --> 00:36:21,324
Mr. Baddington?

627
00:36:22,791 --> 00:36:24,168
There's nothing here.

628
00:36:24,326 --> 00:36:26,533
Oh, it's here, all right.

629
00:36:26,695 --> 00:36:28,470
We're directly above the coordinates.

630
00:36:28,630 --> 00:36:30,041
We would see it, don't you think?

631
00:36:30,199 --> 00:36:33,544
Oh, of course.
Silly-billy me.

632
00:36:33,702 --> 00:36:37,809
Clearly, there is nothing there.
I mean, any rational person

633
00:36:37,973 --> 00:36:40,317
would see that there
is nothing beneath us

634
00:36:40,475 --> 00:36:42,887
but a bunch of mountains and snow.

635
00:36:43,045 --> 00:36:46,993
And not a clever facade
masking Santa's workshop.

636
00:36:47,149 --> 00:36:50,619
Surely not.
Only a madman would think

637
00:36:50,786 --> 00:36:55,326
we'll surely crash and explode
into fiery bits and pieces

638
00:36:55,490 --> 00:36:58,664
if we flew straight down...

639
00:37:00,062 --> 00:37:01,973
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

640
00:37:11,540 --> 00:37:13,349
Aha!

641
00:37:17,879 --> 00:37:20,860
Merry Christmas to me!

642
00:37:25,487 --> 00:37:28,263
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)</font>

643
00:37:33,829 --> 00:37:35,831
<font color="#D900D9">(ANGRY SHOUTING)</font>

644
00:37:35,998 --> 00:37:37,841
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

645
00:37:46,942 --> 00:37:49,582
Excuse me!
Excuse me, coming through!

646
00:37:57,586 --> 00:37:59,293
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

647
00:38:08,964 --> 00:38:11,274
<font color="#D900D9">(NEVILLE CACKLING)</font>

648
00:38:11,433 --> 00:38:13,470
Oh, it wouldn't be Christmas

649
00:38:13,635 --> 00:38:17,481
without complete chaos and utter panic.

650
00:38:17,639 --> 00:38:20,882
<font color="#D900D9">(INHALES DEEPLY)</font>
Do you smell that?

651
00:38:21,043 --> 00:38:22,420
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Cookies?

652
00:38:22,577 --> 00:38:24,147
Hot cocoa?

653
00:38:24,313 --> 00:38:27,954
Hmm, well you can
smell those things, too.

654
00:38:28,116 --> 00:38:32,997
But the more palpable odor
is that of vindication.

655
00:38:33,822 --> 00:38:35,392
- Sorry!
- Hey!

656
00:38:35,557 --> 00:38:38,333
<font color="#808080">NEVILLE:</font> There'll be plenty
of time for pancakes later.

657
00:38:38,493 --> 00:38:41,201
First, find the sleigh!

658
00:38:42,631 --> 00:38:44,131
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Come on! Give it up!
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

659
00:38:44,132 --> 00:38:46,169
Where's the sleigh, round boy?

660
00:38:49,171 --> 00:38:50,844
Yeah! Where's the sleigh?

661
00:38:51,006 --> 00:38:54,818
<font color="#808080">SANTA:</font> You two are not
being very good this year.

662
00:38:54,976 --> 00:38:57,650
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

663
00:38:59,848 --> 00:39:01,191
<font color="#D900D9">(CACKLING)</font>

664
00:39:01,350 --> 00:39:03,023
<font color="#D900D9">(NEVILLE CONTINUING, INDISTINCT)</font>

665
00:39:09,958 --> 00:39:13,303
<font color="#D900D9">(NEVILLE, THROUGH DOOR)</font>
We've so much to discuss.

666
00:39:17,966 --> 00:39:20,845
We have something
in common, you and I.

667
00:39:21,002 --> 00:39:23,539
We're both in the delivery business.

668
00:39:23,705 --> 00:39:26,208
But unlike some lazy-pants

669
00:39:26,375 --> 00:39:29,481
jelly-bellied holiday showboats,

670
00:39:29,644 --> 00:39:34,559
we operate 365 days a year.

671
00:39:34,716 --> 00:39:36,696
It's hard to believe,
but once upon a time,

672
00:39:36,852 --> 00:39:39,389
Christmas was my favorite holiday.

673
00:39:39,554 --> 00:39:42,160
Singing carols,
eating fresh cookies...

674
00:39:42,324 --> 00:39:45,328
Oh, the memories.

675
00:39:45,494 --> 00:39:48,236
You know, that for years,
I looked up to you?

676
00:39:48,397 --> 00:39:52,311
I wanted to be
just... like... you.

677
00:39:53,635 --> 00:39:56,411
You were such a good boy.

678
00:39:56,571 --> 00:39:58,016
What happened to you?

679
00:39:58,173 --> 00:40:01,017
Hah! All-knowing, are we?

680
00:40:01,176 --> 00:40:02,883
Clearly not.

681
00:40:03,044 --> 00:40:05,718
What happened?
I grew up.

682
00:40:05,881 --> 00:40:08,418
I saw through your phony generosity,

683
00:40:08,583 --> 00:40:10,893
giving your worthless toys away,

684
00:40:11,052 --> 00:40:15,398
keeping naive children
drunk with sugary sweets,

685
00:40:15,557 --> 00:40:19,164
while you keep all of the
good stuff to yourself!

686
00:40:19,327 --> 00:40:20,863
I don't know what
you're talking about.

687
00:40:21,029 --> 00:40:22,736
Oh, no?

688
00:40:22,898 --> 00:40:26,368
How do you make it all around
the world in one night?

689
00:40:26,535 --> 00:40:29,607
Huh? Or fit all of those presents

690
00:40:29,771 --> 00:40:32,217
into one bag? Huh? Huh?

691
00:40:32,374 --> 00:40:34,047
How do you fly?

692
00:40:34,209 --> 00:40:36,246
How do you live forever?

693
00:40:36,411 --> 00:40:38,186
Huh? Huh? Huh?

694
00:40:38,346 --> 00:40:39,620
- Stop that!
- Sorry, sir.

695
00:40:39,781 --> 00:40:42,091
Every year, I wrote to you,

696
00:40:42,250 --> 00:40:43,923
asking for the answers,

697
00:40:44,085 --> 00:40:46,691
And all you ever gave me were toys.

698
00:40:48,123 --> 00:40:52,265
This Christmas, I will
have my Christmas wish!

699
00:40:52,427 --> 00:40:55,840
I will give the secrets
of your sleigh to my mother,

700
00:40:56,031 --> 00:40:59,740
and Quickest Airborne Delivery
will be, at last,

701
00:40:59,901 --> 00:41:05,317
the fastest delivery service on Earth!

702
00:41:05,474 --> 00:41:08,216
<font color="#D900D9">(RADIO SQUAWKING)</font>

703
00:41:08,376 --> 00:41:12,119
Neville! Pick up, you
moon-faced feather-brain!

704
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:15,921
Excuse me, I have a business, uh...

705
00:41:16,084 --> 00:41:19,827
A foreign dignitary client
important person.

706
00:41:19,988 --> 00:41:21,934
- That needs my...
<i>- Neville!</i>

707
00:41:23,959 --> 00:41:27,236
<i>Pick up the radio,
you dunder-headed dolt!</i>

708
00:41:27,395 --> 00:41:29,272
Oh, hello, Mommy.

709
00:41:29,431 --> 00:41:30,910
Good news.

710
00:41:31,066 --> 00:41:33,603
I found Santa's workshop.

711
00:41:34,503 --> 00:41:36,881
Have you, now?

712
00:41:37,072 --> 00:41:39,177
<font color="#D900D9">(BERNARD WHISPERING)</font> Santa!

713
00:41:40,242 --> 00:41:43,018
Santa, it's me, Bernard.

714
00:41:43,178 --> 00:41:47,149
Bernard! <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>
Clever disguise.

715
00:41:47,315 --> 00:41:49,454
Do you think you can
get us out of here?

716
00:41:49,618 --> 00:41:51,996
He's after the Time Globe.

717
00:41:52,153 --> 00:41:53,291
I have a better idea.

718
00:41:53,455 --> 00:41:55,332
I think I know a way to stop him,

719
00:41:55,490 --> 00:41:57,010
but I'm gonna have to go back in time.

720
00:41:57,158 --> 00:41:58,660
Again.

721
00:41:58,827 --> 00:42:00,829
Bernard! Be careful!

722
00:42:00,996 --> 00:42:03,636
I told you.
You can't undo the past.

723
00:42:03,798 --> 00:42:06,210
- Only add to it.
- I have to try.

724
00:42:06,368 --> 00:42:09,144
If I can stop myself from making
it to the presentation, I can...

725
00:42:09,304 --> 00:42:10,612
Who are you talking to?

726
00:42:11,540 --> 00:42:12,644
Ow!

727
00:42:12,807 --> 00:42:13,808
I see with that thing!

728
00:42:13,975 --> 00:42:15,318
- How do you like it?
- Ow!

729
00:42:15,477 --> 00:42:16,615
I... Little...

730
00:42:16,778 --> 00:42:18,621
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL SHOUTING)</font> Come here, you!

731
00:42:18,780 --> 00:42:19,884
Gotcha!

732
00:42:23,852 --> 00:42:25,798
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

733
00:42:28,723 --> 00:42:30,566
Great. Dead end.

734
00:42:31,793 --> 00:42:33,238
<font color="#D900D9">(DOLL SQUEAKS)</font>

735
00:42:33,395 --> 00:42:34,840
<font color="#D900D9">(GUN BEEPS)</font>

736
00:42:34,996 --> 00:42:36,566
<font color="#D900D9">(SAGS)</font>

737
00:42:36,731 --> 00:42:38,506
Come out, little elf.

738
00:42:38,667 --> 00:42:40,340
There's nowhere to run.

739
00:42:40,502 --> 00:42:41,810
And you wouldn't get very far

740
00:42:41,970 --> 00:42:44,849
on those stubby little legs of yours.

741
00:42:49,044 --> 00:42:52,253
Ah. Don't mind if I do.

742
00:42:54,649 --> 00:42:56,959
<font color="#D900D9">(ENGINE ROARS)</font>
What's that sound?

743
00:42:58,019 --> 00:42:59,589
<font color="#D900D9">(HORN TOOTS)</font>

744
00:43:00,889 --> 00:43:02,266
I'm going back, Santa!

745
00:43:02,424 --> 00:43:03,824
If I can destroy the memory device,

746
00:43:03,925 --> 00:43:05,996
I can stop the presentation!

747
00:43:06,161 --> 00:43:07,663
Good luck, Bernard!

748
00:43:07,829 --> 00:43:10,036
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font> Don't move, Beardy.

749
00:43:10,198 --> 00:43:12,007
<font color="#D900D9">(EXCLAIMING)</font>

750
00:43:14,402 --> 00:43:15,881
<font color="#D900D9">(TIRES SCREECHING)</font>

751
00:43:17,105 --> 00:43:18,345
<font color="#D900D9">(GIGGLING)</font>

752
00:43:23,645 --> 00:43:25,249
Get that elf!

753
00:43:26,848 --> 00:43:28,919
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH YELL)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

754
00:43:38,593 --> 00:43:39,765
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

755
00:43:47,202 --> 00:43:48,237
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

756
00:43:54,376 --> 00:43:56,617
Snow long!
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLING)</font>

757
00:43:58,013 --> 00:43:59,390
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

758
00:44:01,116 --> 00:44:02,390
They're coming!

759
00:44:03,652 --> 00:44:05,325
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font> Come here!

760
00:44:07,922 --> 00:44:09,299
- Move it in!
- Here, here!

761
00:44:09,457 --> 00:44:12,301
- Go, go, go!
- Yes!

762
00:44:15,430 --> 00:44:18,036
Come on, Bernard,
just a few more seconds!

763
00:44:18,233 --> 00:44:20,509
<font color="#D900D9">(ISSUING COMMAND)</font>

764
00:44:20,669 --> 00:44:21,773
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

765
00:44:23,471 --> 00:44:25,508
Deck the halls, I made it!

766
00:44:27,342 --> 00:44:29,583
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

767
00:44:31,312 --> 00:44:33,155
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

768
00:44:34,115 --> 00:44:36,152
What did you do that for?

769
00:44:36,317 --> 00:44:37,660
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> He's activated the sleigh!

770
00:44:39,954 --> 00:44:42,457
<font color="#808080">OTHER BERNARD:</font> I have?
How did I do that?

771
00:44:43,491 --> 00:44:44,492
<font color="#D900D9">(YELPS)</font>

772
00:44:44,659 --> 00:44:46,366
- Get it!
- Follow me!

773
00:44:46,528 --> 00:44:49,304
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CLAMORING)</font>

774
00:44:50,331 --> 00:44:51,469
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

775
00:45:05,113 --> 00:45:10,222
Oh, my whole life and I had to
repeat this day three times.

776
00:45:12,487 --> 00:45:14,296
<font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERING)</font> Watch out for the...
<font color="#D900D9">(SQUISH)</font>

777
00:45:14,456 --> 00:45:17,994
Oh, come on, I just
cleaned up in here.

778
00:45:18,159 --> 00:45:20,799
Well, duh,
you went back in time.

779
00:45:31,339 --> 00:45:34,320
<font color="#D900D9">(SNORING LOUDLY)</font>

780
00:45:49,390 --> 00:45:51,529
Nah, too loud.

781
00:45:52,594 --> 00:45:54,574
<font color="#D900D9">(ALARM CLANGING)</font>

782
00:45:54,729 --> 00:45:57,039
<font color="#808080">OTHER BERNARD:</font> What are you doing here?

783
00:45:59,267 --> 00:46:02,942
I expressly ordered
nine ladies dancing.

784
00:46:07,075 --> 00:46:08,383
<font color="#D900D9">(RESUMES SNORING)</font>

785
00:46:29,130 --> 00:46:31,770
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font> I told you.

786
00:46:31,933 --> 00:46:35,574
You're looking at the world's
first time-traveling elf.

787
00:46:38,873 --> 00:46:41,581
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CHATTER)</font>

788
00:46:45,780 --> 00:46:47,657
Excuse you!

789
00:46:47,816 --> 00:46:49,955
You don't eat it, you just...

790
00:47:00,395 --> 00:47:02,068
<font color="#D900D9">(EXCLAIMING)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(THUMP)</font>

791
00:47:02,230 --> 00:47:05,074
<font color="#D900D9">(SLEEPY MUTTERING)</font>

792
00:47:14,909 --> 00:47:16,354
Oh no!

793
00:47:16,511 --> 00:47:18,991
Mint chocolate cookies,
I slept in!

794
00:47:19,147 --> 00:47:21,024
Not today, not today!

795
00:47:21,182 --> 00:47:23,321
Oh, where the blinking...?

796
00:47:23,484 --> 00:47:25,020
Ah, there you are.
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

797
00:47:28,823 --> 00:47:31,633
Oh, now I'll never stop
the presentation!

798
00:47:32,861 --> 00:47:33,862
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL EXCLAIMING)</font>

799
00:47:34,028 --> 00:47:36,099
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font> No pants!

800
00:47:36,231 --> 00:47:37,938
No pants!

801
00:47:53,381 --> 00:47:54,451
<font color="#D900D9">(YELPS)</font>

802
00:47:56,684 --> 00:47:57,822
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

803
00:48:00,688 --> 00:48:02,167
- Huh?
- Huh?

804
00:48:04,225 --> 00:48:05,898
<font color="#D900D9">(PANTING)</font>

805
00:48:08,997 --> 00:48:10,533
I've got a presentation to stop.

806
00:48:12,967 --> 00:48:15,140
If I could just get there first!

807
00:48:21,209 --> 00:48:23,189
Ooh, this is gonna sting!

808
00:48:26,481 --> 00:48:28,358
<font color="#D900D9">(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS)</font>
Wait! Wait up!

809
00:48:31,486 --> 00:48:33,727
Wait up!
Hold the train!

810
00:48:34,589 --> 00:48:35,795
Ooh!

811
00:48:53,341 --> 00:48:54,945
Oh, sorry!

812
00:49:00,615 --> 00:49:02,788
<font color="#D900D9">(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING)</font>

813
00:49:08,289 --> 00:49:09,359
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

814
00:49:15,763 --> 00:49:16,935
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font>

815
00:49:19,267 --> 00:49:21,042
That way!

816
00:49:26,541 --> 00:49:28,452
Ooh!

817
00:49:30,979 --> 00:49:32,925
Morning, Blitz!

818
00:49:39,387 --> 00:49:42,630
<font color="#D900D9">(BERNARD GROANS)</font> Ow!

819
00:49:42,790 --> 00:49:44,633
<font color="#D900D9">(INQUISITIVE GIBBERISH)</font>

820
00:49:45,893 --> 00:49:47,839
How long have I been out?

821
00:49:50,565 --> 00:49:53,011
Oh, great! It happened again!

822
00:49:53,167 --> 00:49:55,647
Ow! What'd you do that for, anyway?

823
00:49:55,803 --> 00:49:57,840
Jumping on me like that.
Have you lost your mind?

824
00:49:58,006 --> 00:49:59,485
<font color="#D900D9">(GIBBERISH)</font>

825
00:49:59,640 --> 00:50:01,313
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font> Me?

826
00:50:01,476 --> 00:50:04,821
It was my fault?
You are ridiculous.

827
00:50:04,979 --> 00:50:07,823
<font color="#808080">BERNARD 2:</font> <i>Listen,
you have to find the other me.</i>

828
00:50:07,982 --> 00:50:10,861
<i>Stop me and get me to listen
to you, no matter what!</i>

829
00:50:11,019 --> 00:50:12,498
It was my fault.

830
00:50:12,653 --> 00:50:16,362
You just got the wrong "me."
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

831
00:50:16,524 --> 00:50:19,266
What's the point of
having a time machine

832
00:50:19,427 --> 00:50:22,067
if you can't go back and
prevent things from happening?

833
00:50:22,263 --> 00:50:23,469
<font color="#D900D9">(POWER GRID HUMMING)</font>

834
00:50:23,631 --> 00:50:25,668
Hah! There are the lights!

835
00:50:25,833 --> 00:50:28,541
Brilliant! Disaster
is right on schedule!

836
00:50:28,703 --> 00:50:32,207
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(INQUISITIVE GIBBERISH)</font>

837
00:50:34,175 --> 00:50:37,054
Oh, just leave me alone, would you?

838
00:50:38,346 --> 00:50:39,950
You should stay away.

839
00:50:40,114 --> 00:50:41,684
As far away from me as possible,

840
00:50:41,849 --> 00:50:43,453
if you know what's good for you.

841
00:50:45,820 --> 00:50:47,231
Just go back to the stables

842
00:50:47,388 --> 00:50:49,766
before I mess everything
up for you, too.

843
00:50:50,958 --> 00:50:53,564
Can't you see what
a muck-up I am?

844
00:50:55,730 --> 00:50:58,574
Go... Go on, Blitz.
Go on, will you?

845
00:50:58,733 --> 00:51:00,872
Go!

846
00:51:08,376 --> 00:51:12,347
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Santech is only for
the greatest elf minds, not...

847
00:51:12,513 --> 00:51:15,926
<font color="#D900D9">(INHALES)</font>
...reindeer poop-scoopers.

848
00:51:18,352 --> 00:51:20,764
Could this day get any worse?

849
00:51:20,922 --> 00:51:22,367
<font color="#D900D9">(ZAPPING)</font>
<font color="#808080">BERNARD 1:</font> Ow!

850
00:51:24,392 --> 00:51:26,269
<font color="#D900D9">(BERNARD 1 GRUNTS)</font>

851
00:51:30,264 --> 00:51:32,835
<font color="#808080">SNOWY:</font> Wake up, Bernard!

852
00:51:33,534 --> 00:51:34,877
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

853
00:51:35,036 --> 00:51:38,108
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

854
00:51:38,272 --> 00:51:40,343
Thought you could get away, did you?

855
00:51:40,508 --> 00:51:43,955
Well, Bernard, if you
are indeed innocent,

856
00:51:44,112 --> 00:51:46,023
how do you explain this?

857
00:51:46,180 --> 00:51:49,184
Huh? We found this outside Santech.

858
00:51:49,317 --> 00:51:51,593
We believe that you intentionally
caused the blackout

859
00:51:51,752 --> 00:51:53,698
that disabled the cloaking hologram!

860
00:51:53,855 --> 00:51:58,304
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font> I'm not the one you
should be worried about.

861
00:51:58,459 --> 00:52:03,431
Neville Baddington. He's the one
you should be worried about.

862
00:52:03,598 --> 00:52:05,942
- Who's that?
- Neville Baddington.

863
00:52:06,100 --> 00:52:08,273
Height: six foot one.

864
00:52:08,436 --> 00:52:10,040
Weight: blah, blah, blah.

865
00:52:10,204 --> 00:52:12,047
Oh, here we go!

866
00:52:12,206 --> 00:52:15,813
Heir to the Quickest
Airborne Delivery empire.

867
00:52:15,977 --> 00:52:19,049
<font color="#D900D9">(FANFARE PLAYS)</font>

868
00:52:19,213 --> 00:52:21,124
<font color="#808080">WOMAN ON SCREEN:</font> <i>Globe-trotting millionaire</i>

869
00:52:21,282 --> 00:52:23,091
<i>and all-around eccentric heir</i>

870
00:52:23,251 --> 00:52:25,322
<i>to the Quickest Airborne
delivery service,</i>

871
00:52:25,486 --> 00:52:28,831
<i>Neville Baddington claims
"I can find Santa Claus."</i>

872
00:52:28,990 --> 00:52:30,857
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> <i>You heard it right, folks.</i>

873
00:52:30,858 --> 00:52:33,304
<i>This particular purveyor of parcels</i>

874
00:52:33,461 --> 00:52:36,999
<i>looks to unlock the secrets
of Santa's speedy sleigh.</i>

875
00:52:37,165 --> 00:52:39,736
<font color="#808080">NEVILLE ON SCREEN:</font> <i>I've been
documenting him for years.</i>

876
00:52:39,901 --> 00:52:44,441
<i>I have photographic proof
here, here and here.</i>

877
00:52:44,605 --> 00:52:46,642
- Hmm?
- That's him.

878
00:52:46,807 --> 00:52:48,480
He wants to learn how Santa

879
00:52:48,643 --> 00:52:51,487
travels round the world
in one night

880
00:52:51,646 --> 00:52:53,990
<font color="#D900D9">(BUZZING)</font>
- <font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

881
00:52:55,283 --> 00:52:57,763
Sir! I think we've got a blip!

882
00:52:57,919 --> 00:52:59,296
A blip?

883
00:52:59,453 --> 00:53:01,660
Uh, I think it looks
more like a blop.

884
00:53:03,524 --> 00:53:06,596
<font color="#808080">NEVILLE:</font> Oh, of course!
Silly-billy me.

885
00:53:06,761 --> 00:53:11,176
Clearly, there is nothing there.
I mean, any rational person

886
00:53:11,332 --> 00:53:13,312
would see that there
is nothing beneath us

887
00:53:13,467 --> 00:53:16,175
but a bunch of mountains and snow.

888
00:53:16,337 --> 00:53:20,308
And not a clever facade
masking Santa's workshop.

889
00:53:20,474 --> 00:53:23,648
Surely not.
Only a madman would think

890
00:53:23,811 --> 00:53:28,658
we will surely crash and explode
into fiery bits and pieces

891
00:53:28,816 --> 00:53:31,956
if we flew straight down...

892
00:53:33,688 --> 00:53:35,668
<font color="#D900D9">(YELLING)</font>

893
00:53:48,169 --> 00:53:51,048
<font color="#D900D9">(KLAXON SOUNDING)</font>

894
00:53:51,205 --> 00:53:53,583
Sir, someone has
